# @SHBMV04P083A_BEG_WAANH
VAR_SMJXV01P660A VAR_MYWXV07P421A VAR_MYWXV08P052A VAR_NSSXV02P216A VAR_BQMXV11P073A VAR_MZTXV19P215B VAR_MZTXV26P063A حدثنا أبو بكر قال نا @TR1_AANH@ عبد الله بن نمير عن محمد بن إسحاق عن ثور عن عبد الله بن أبي صالح عن صفية بنت شيبة عن عائشة قالت قال رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم لا طلاق ولا عتاق في إغلاق. @SHBMV04P083A_END_WAANH
PageV04P083
# @COMMENT: Passage not found in HSNX. The tradition is set during the ḥajj when ʿAdī b. ʿAdī al-Kindī advised Muḥammad b. ʿUbayd b. Abī Ṣāliḥ al-Makkī to go collect a tradition from Ṣafīyah bint Shaybah b. ʿUthmān b. Abī Ṭalḥah. Muḥammad b. ʿUbayd b. Abī Ṣāliḥ and ʿAdī b. ʿAdī al-Kindī are not mentioned in HSNX. Ṣafīyah bint Shaybah b. ʿUthmān is mentioned in HSNXV02P411C regarding the Conquest of Mecca (also see via WSACD NYMXV06P3378A). Thawr b. Yazīd al-Kalāʿī, Abū Khālid, is mentioned three times by WZATB (HSNXV01P166A, HSNXV01P308A, and HSNXV01P634C). According to Muḥammad b. Saʿd, he was from the people of Ḥimṣ and died in Jerusalem in 153/770 at the age of 60. His grandfather fought for Muʿāwiyah at Ṣiffīn against ʿAlī (TKXXV07P324A). Muḥammad b. ʿUbayd b. Abī Ṣāliḥ al-Makkī is mentioned in BKHBV01P171C, HJKXV01P583A, BNTHV07P371C, and MZTXV19P215A only in relation to this tradition, although the latter source states that he also related from Mujāhid b. Jabr al-Makkī and in addition to Thawr b. Yazīd al-Ḥimṣī, he also related to Mujāhid b. Jabr al-Makkī. According to HJRBV09P330A he lived in Jerusalem. No date of death is mentioned. ʿAdī b. ʿAdī b. ʿUmayrah al-Kindī al-Shaybānī, Abū Farwah al-Jazīrī, was a member of the al-Ḥārith b. Muʿāwiyah b. Thawr tribe. Described as pious by al-Ṭabarī, he commanded troops under Muḥammad b. Marwān against Khārijī rebels in 76/ 695 (TBRBV06P243A). He is described as a partisan of the Umayyads and was appointed as commander of Mūsil, the Jazīrah, and then Armīnīyah by ʿUmar b. ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz (TDSHV40P137A, although MZTXV19P5354B states this was done by Sulaymān b. ʿAbd al-Mālik). He was included among the 3rd generation of successors in the Jazīrah and to have been trustworthy (ibid., 138). He died in 120/738 according to al-Dhahabī and others (DHBRV01P116D). 
Ṣafīyah bint Shaybah b. ʿUthmān b. Abī Ṭalḥah was a Meccan companion and related from many of the Prophet's wives and related to many in the first generation of successors. No date of death is mentioned (see, MZTXV35P212B). One of the most comonly quoted traditions in the Ibn Isḥāq corpus. Passage also found in WSACD, WZAZA, and WASMR. Unable to place the date of the event in which the tradition was collected in Mecca. Most likely to be placed in the opinions of Muḥammad in fiqh section. 

